---
import BaseHead from '../components/BaseHead.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
import Header from '../components/Header.astro';
import { SITE_DESCRIPTION, SITE_TITLE } from '../consts';
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
	<head>
		<BaseHead title={SITE_TITLE} description={SITE_DESCRIPTION} />
	</head>
	<body>
		<Header />
		<main>
			<h1>Welcome! 👋</h1>
			<p>
				I am <strong>Neerav Kumar</strong>, a Data Engineer focused on distributed systems, storage formats, and understanding the core mechanics of massive-scale analytics.
			</p>
			<p>
				This is my personal digital garden where I tear down tools like Apache Spark and Parquet to understand exactly <i>how</i> they work beneath their APIs. I believe that scaling data pipelines isn't just about writing code; it's about deeply understanding the tradeoffs of the architecture you are building upon.
			</p>
			<p>Check out my latest architectural deep-dives in the <strong><a href="/blog">Blog</a></strong> section, where I explore the evolution of Big Data storage, network execution, and more.</p>
			<ul>
				<li><a href="/blog/parquet-evolution/">Apache Parquet: A Decade of Architectural Evolution</a></li>
				<li><a href="/blog/spark-broadcast-evolution/">Demystifying Spark Broadcast: A Pragmatic Architecture Evolution</a></li>
			</ul>
			<p>If you'd like to read more about my background, check out the <a href="/about">About</a> page or connect with me via the GitHub link in the header!</p>
		</main>
		<Footer />
	</body>
</html>
